Hello! I am a PathPlanner rookie and I am struggling to get my robot to drive correctly. I have been messing with the PID values, maximum velocity, and maximum acceleration, but I have not been able to get the two curves pictured below to match.

The path that returned the data below is commanding the robot to drive 1m straight, but the robot is going anywhere between 65 and 80cm. I have tried to follow some youtube tutorials on how to tune a PID controller, but when I increase the P or I values enough to match the two curves while the commanded value is increasing, my actual value diverges.

The link to my code is also attached below. If anyone has any suggestions or could help me find something I missed, it would be greatly appreciated.
